ion, which have similar consequences in forming both public and professional opinion, shape the politics of the abortion debates has until recently received very little attention.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aHEALTH & FITNESS / Pregnancy & Childbirth.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150361608040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503616080423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503616080/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles